.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH k2i-table 1  "k2i-table "
.SH NAME
k2i\-table \- Register or reset table data
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBk2i\-table\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Register or reset table data
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
k2i\-table\-register(1)
Register existing Parquet files without copying them
.TP
k2i\-table\-reset(1)
Reset a registered table
.TP
k2i\-table\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  k2i table register \-\-config config.toml \-\-database f1 \-\-table derived_state \-\-source \*(Aq/data/*.parquet\*(Aq
  k2i table reset \-\-config config.toml \-\-database f1 \-\-table derived_state \-\-keep\-data
